article.headline: Leissner's season-high sparks UNH romp over Dartmouth, 83-66
article.linkText: Leissner's season-high sparks UNH romp over Dartmouth, 83-66
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Tanner Leissner scored a season-high 32 points, hitting all four of his shots from behind the three-point arc, combining with Jacoby Armstrong to score 53 points and New Hampshire rolled over in-state rival Dartmouth, 83-66 to win the Battle of the Granite State Saturday night. The pair helped the Wildcats shoot 50 percent (27 of 54) from the field. Leissner hit 9 of 16, including 4 of 4 from deep, while Armstrong was 8 of 10 from the floor and 4 of 4 from the line. UNH (4-10) built a 15-point lead by intermission, 45-30, and Leissner hit two of the Wildcats three-straight 3-pointers to push the lead to 20 points, 54-34 three minutes into the second half. Overall, UNH knocked down 12 of the 26 three-point attempts and held a 35-26 advantage on the boards. Miles Wright led Dartmouth (4-7) with 14 points. Will Emery added 12.
